%html
  %head
    %meta{charset: "utf-8"}/
    %meta{content: "IE=edge,chrome=1", http: {equiv: "X-UA-Compatible"}}
    %meta{name: "viewport", content: "initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1"}

    %title Hydra Development, Inc
    %link{href: "assets/stylesheets/application.css", rel: "stylesheet", type: "text/css"}

  %body
    .hero
      .background-overlay
      .intro
        %h1 Hydra Development
        %h2 Web Applications Done Right

    .hero-callout
      %section.banner
        %h5.tagline Building beautiful scalable applications
        %a.cta{href: "mailto:hello@hydradev.co?Subject=I%20would%20like%20to%20hire%20Hydra"}
          Get in Touch

    %section.company-description
      %header
        %h5.what-we-do
          We build minimum viable products &amp; help you reach the scale of success.
    %hr
    %section.company-info
      .header
        %h2.values Methodology and Core Values
      .cards
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-header
              %h4.toolset Extreme Programming
            .card-content
              %p By employing test-driven development, pair programming and constant refactoring, we deliver the highest quality software possible.
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-header
              %h4.toolset Ruby, CoffeeScript and Go
            .card-content
              %p By pairing the flexibility of dynamic languages with the type-safety and speed of Go, we can squeeze the most out of any application.
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-header
              %h4.toolset Mentoring
            .card-content
              %p By sharing sharing knowledge and collaborating, we spread the seeds of innovation.
      %hr
      .header
        %h2 Recent Clients
      .cards
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-image
              %img{ alt: '', src: "http://photos.faun.me/photos/i-54PZmwR/0/X2/i-54PZmwR-M.jpg" }/
            .card-header
              %h3.client-name Neo
              %h5.project-type Team Augmentation
            .card-content
              %p For Neo, we augmented an existing team to contribute to a next-generation publishing platform for scientific journals. During the course of this project, we:
              %ul
                %li Improved code quality notification and continuous integration stability
                %li Created an external service to convert ePub documents to PDF and deliver them to application users after conversion
                %li Generated Ansible playbook and provisioning scripts for deploying application to Amazon EC2
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-image
              %img{ alt: '', src: "http://photos.faun.me/photos/i-Lg4QKFj/0/X2/i-Lg4QKFj-M.jpg" }/
            .card-header
              %h3.client-name Timeline Labs
              %h5.project-type Greenfield Build
            .card-content
              %p For Timeline Labs, we built a world-class sentiment analysis tool that helped news organizations and celebrities understand the sentiment and level of user engagement throughout the world. During the course of this project, we:
              %ul
                %li Created a startup from a prototype that eventually was aquired
                %li Built a robust content management system for managing application administration and permissions
                %li Consumed statistics from a Python API and displayed time-series graphs using D3.js and Rickshaw.js using Angular.js with streaming updates via websockets
        %aside.card
          %article
            .card-image
              %img{ alt: '', src: "http://photos.faun.me/Events/Camping-at-Angel-Island/i-3VTSrQx/1/M/_MG_3750-M.jpg" }/
            .card-header
              %h3.client-name Afolio
              %h5.project-type Rescue Project
            .card-content
              %p For Afolio, we helped to fixup a rescue project with legacy codebase and low test coverage. During the course of this project, we:
              %ul
                %li Significantly improved test coverage
                %li Re-routed file uploads from direct application pass-through to a cloud server via direct upload with push notifications and background job processing
                %li Increased file upload capacity and reliability while meanwhile significantly decreasing file upload time allowing for greater customer satisfaction and retention

